## Proposed Changes

### Python Backend — Training Pipeline

#### [MODIFY] [main.py](file:///c:/Users/91974/Downloads/plant_leaf_desease-main%20(1)/plant_leaf_desease-main/python_backend/main.py)

Add 4 new endpoints + modify existing ones:

**New endpoints:**

1. **`POST /segment-for-training`** — Upload whole tree images → YOLOv8s-seg segments individual leaves → returns cropped leaf images as base64 + bounding boxes. The frontend shows these crops for the user to label.

2. **`POST /save-training-leaves`** — Receives labeled leaf crops (base64 image + disease label) → saves them to disk organized by class folders: `training_data/{class_name}/leaf_001.jpg`

3. **`POST /train-custom-model`** — Fine-tunes MobileNetV2 on the saved leaf images using PyTorch:
   - Loads all images from `training_data/` folders
   - Train/val split (80/20)
   - Fine-tunes for N epochs with early stopping
   - Saves model to `custom_model.pth`
   - Returns real-time training metrics (loss, accuracy, confidence per epoch)
   - Target: 100% training accuracy

4. **`GET /training-status`** — Returns current training progress, metrics, and whether a custom model exists

**Modified endpoints:**

- **`/analyze-vision`** — If a custom fine-tuned model exists (`custom_model.pth`), use it instead of the default PlantVillage model. This ensures predictions use your trained model.

