## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Disease classes for labeling**: Which diseases should appear in the labeling dropdown? Options:
> - A) Full PlantVillage 38 classes (Apple Scab, Tomato Early Blight, etc.)
> - B) Simplified set (Healthy, Early Blight, Late Blight, Powdery Mildew, Rust, Bacterial Spot, Leaf Mold)
> - C) Custom classes that you define?

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Training data volume**: How many whole tree/plant images will you typically upload for training? This affects whether we need batch processing or can handle it in-memory. (10-50 images? 100+? 500+?)

> [!NOTE]
> **CPU fine-tuning feasibility**: MobileNetV2 is small enough to fine-tune on CPU (HF Spaces). With ~200-500 leaf images, training 20 epochs takes ~5-10 minutes on CPU. With >1000 images, it could take 20-30 min. This is acceptable for a one-time training run.

## Verification Plan

### Accuracy Targets
- **Training data**: Fine-tune until training accuracy reaches ~100% (overfit intentionally, per professor's requirement)
- **Test data (new trees)**: Each leaf classification should show >70% confidence; leaves below threshold get flagged

### Tests
1. Upload 5 whole tree images → verify each gets segmented into individual leaves
2. Label 50+ leaves → trigger training → verify training accuracy reaches ~100%
3. Upload new tree image → verify each leaf classified with >70% confidence
4. Upload non-plant image → verify CLIP gate rejects it
